671
00:29:08,792 --> 00:29:11,083
INTERVIEWER:<i> And you developed</i>
<i>a lot of your own single stuff</i>

672
00:29:11,167 --> 00:29:12,959
<i>at the Cafe Au Go Go, was it?</i>

673
00:29:13,042 --> 00:29:15,334
Down in Greenwich Village.
Yeah, I got tired of going out

674
00:29:15,417 --> 00:29:18,667
to Indianapolis and Detroit
and St. Louis for one week,

675
00:29:18,751 --> 00:29:20,500
and not having anything
to show for it.

676
00:29:20,584 --> 00:29:21,918
You spend all your money
traveling.

677
00:29:22,000 --> 00:29:23,876
So I decided to stay
in New York for a year,

678
00:29:23,959 --> 00:29:25,042
and work at one club

679
00:29:25,125 --> 00:29:27,334
where I could develop
my style and my material.

680
00:29:27,417 --> 00:29:28,959
And it happened
in Greenwich Village

681
00:29:29,042 --> 00:29:30,334
at the Go Go.
This is the theater

682
00:29:30,417 --> 00:29:32,542
where I first did television
for Merv Griffin,

683
00:29:32,626 --> 00:29:33,959
-where it really began.
-INTERVIEWER: Right.

684
00:29:34,042 --> 00:29:35,876
The Indian Sergeant
was the first character.

685
00:29:35,959 --> 00:29:38,542
He used to work with a partner,
and now, he's on his own.

686
00:29:38,626 --> 00:29:40,626
Another of television's
tadpoles,

687
00:29:40,709 --> 00:29:42,792
the kind of talent
always welcome around here.

688
00:29:42,876 --> 00:29:46,542
Would you all meet
young George Carlin. George?

689
00:29:46,626 --> 00:29:53,042
-♪ (BAND MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
-(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

690
00:29:54,083 --> 00:29:56,125
Uh...
I've been watching the Westerns.

691
00:29:56,209 --> 00:29:57,667
All of us have been watching
Western movies,

692
00:29:57,751 --> 00:29:59,959
an endless stream of them,
for our entire lives,

