00:31:13,500 --> 00:31:15,584
<i>I found out
I had to start writing stuff</i>

724
00:31:15,667 --> 00:31:17,250
<i>at a very fast rate.</i>

725
00:31:17,334 --> 00:31:18,292
Right now, we're sending it out

726
00:31:18,375 --> 00:31:19,542
for a little under
three feet tall.

727
00:31:19,626 --> 00:31:21,292
-Happy 35th birthday, Linda.
-(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

728
00:31:21,375 --> 00:31:22,500
GEORGE:<i> I did the disc jockey.</i>

729
00:31:22,584 --> 00:31:24,417
It's a brand new one.
It's called,

730
00:31:24,500 --> 00:31:26,959
"Your face cleared up."

731
00:31:27,042 --> 00:31:29,834
<i>Then I did a newscast,
news, sports, and weather.</i>

732
00:31:29,918 --> 00:31:33,334
<i>Again, demonstrations
and protests dominate
the headlines.</i>

733
00:31:33,417 --> 00:31:34,876
The draft card burners
are at it again.

734
00:31:34,959 --> 00:31:37,209
Not content with burning
their individual draft cards,

735
00:31:37,292 --> 00:31:39,876
several demonstrators today
set fire to the Pentagon.

736
00:31:39,959 --> 00:31:41,042
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

737
00:31:41,125 --> 00:31:43,918
I saw him early.
With a suit and tie,

738
00:31:44,000 --> 00:31:46,083
and it was just--
he was sparkling.

739
00:31:46,167 --> 00:31:48,834
-HOST: How you feel?
-(EXAGGERATED ACCENT) Wonderful.
I'll tell you one thing.

740
00:31:48,918 --> 00:31:51,250
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

741
00:31:51,334 --> 00:31:53,584
-What I said was good?
-HOST: Very good, yes.

742
00:31:53,667 --> 00:31:55,626
ROBERT KLEIN:
<i>He was likeable immediately.</i>

743
00:31:55,709 --> 00:31:56,918
HOST:
I could talk like that too.

744
00:31:57,000 --> 00:31:58,459
-GEORGE: Can you?
-(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

745
00:31:58,542 --> 00:32:03,250
And I think that George Carlin
is one of two autodidacts

746
00:32:03,334 --> 00:32:05,334
in American comedy,
that is to say,

747
00:32:05,417 --> 00:32:09,542
people who are self-taught,
George and Groucho Marx.

748
00:32:09,626 --> 00:32:12,167
<i>I think George proved
in many ways</i>

749
00:32:12,250 --> 00:32:13,375
<i>how intelligent he was,</i>

750
00:32:13,459 --> 00:32:17,167
<i>and how interested he was
in the world around him.</i>

751
00:32:17,250 --> 00:32:18,626
I really haven't been
to the movies

752
00:32:18,709 --> 00:32:20,083
in an awfully long time.

753
00:32:20,167 --> 00:32:23,042
I think the last movie I saw
was<i> West Side Story,</i>

754
00:32:23,125 --> 00:32:25,083
and I was really disappointed
with that

755
00:32:25,167 --> 00:32:26,375
because I'm from the West Side,

756
00:32:26,459 --> 00:32:28,876
and I understood these kids
were supposed to be tough

757
00:32:28,959 --> 00:32:30,792
in the movie. I mean,
two people get killed

758
00:32:30,876 --> 00:32:32,626
in the movie.
They should be tough kids,

759
00:32:32,709 --> 00:32:34,042
but it didn't come off
like that.

760
00:32:34,125 --> 00:32:35,209
It was kind of a...

761
00:32:38,334 --> 00:32:46,042
-(MIMICS UPBEAT MUSIC)
-(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

762
00:32:46,125 --> 00:32:48,042
"Come on, let's go get them.
Let's go get those guys.

763
00:32:48,125 --> 00:32:51,250
Let's go get them and kill them,
but first we're going to dance."

764
00:32:51,334 --> 00:32:55,000
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

765
00:32:55,083 --> 00:33:00,792
-♪ (MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
-(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

766
00:33:00,876 --> 00:33:03,626
GEORGE:<i> In order for me</i>
<i>to follow this mainstream dream,</i>

767
00:33:03,709 --> 00:33:06,209
<i>I had to play their game,</i>

768
00:33:06,292 --> 00:33:09,209
<i>which was,
you had to get on variety shows.</i>

769
00:33:09,292 --> 00:33:13,500
<i>So I went to Hollywood
in 1966 with Kelly and Brenda,</i>

770
00:33:13,584 --> 00:33:15,667
<i>and I did</i>
<i>the</i> Kraft Summer Music Hall.

771
00:33:15,751 --> 00:33:17,417
Hi, I am John Davidson.

772
00:33:17,500 --> 00:33:19,542
<i>Welcome</i>
<i>to the</i> Kraft Summer Music Hall.

773
00:33:19,626 --> 00:33:21,042
We've got some wonderful guests
tonight,

774
00:33:21,125 --> 00:33:22,667
but of course,
the whole gang is right here.

775
00:33:22,751 --> 00:33:24,876
So, let's meet them, huh?
George Carlin.

776
00:33:24,959 --> 00:33:27,751
(AUDIENCE CHEERING, APPLAUDING)

777
00:33:27,834 --> 00:33:29,209
JOHN DAVIDSON: Jackie and Gayle.

778
00:33:31,250 --> 00:33:32,667
The Lively Set.

779
00:33:34,584 --> 00:33:36,626
And our guest,
Mr. Richard Pryor.

780
00:33:38,918 --> 00:33:40,918
Ladies and gentlemen,
you've met our two comedians,

781
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:42,792
George Carlin and Richard Pryor.

782
00:33:42,876 --> 00:33:44,000
-That's right.
-Guys,

783
00:33:44,083 --> 00:33:45,959
earlier, when you were doing
your routines,

784
00:33:46,042 --> 00:33:47,250
at first I was watching you,

785
00:33:47,334 --> 00:33:49,209
-like a nice guy.
-Yeah, yeah.

786
00:33:49,292 --> 00:33:51,709
And then I found
that it was much more fun

787
00:33:51,792 --> 00:33:52,959
to watch the audience.

788
00:33:53,042 --> 00:33:54,584
-The audience?
-Watch the audience?

789
00:33:54,667 --> 00:33:56,000
-Yes.
-While we're working?

790
00:33:56,083 --> 00:33:57,876
Should we leave now,
Richie, man? Let's go.

791
00:33:57,959 --> 00:33:58,959
-No.
-(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

792
00:33:59,042 --> 00:34:00,709
What I mean is I found
it was much more fun

793
00:34:00,792 --> 00:34:01,918
to watch the audience,

794
00:34:02,000 --> 00:34:03,626
because you can see
the different ways

795
00:34:03,709 --> 00:34:04,792
that people laugh.

796
00:34:04,876 --> 00:34:06,125
-Have you ever noticed that?
-Oh, yeah. Yeah.

797
00:34:06,209 --> 00:34:08,000
You must notice
that in the nightclubs, right?

798
00:34:08,083 --> 00:34:09,167
Yeah, well, I have always

799
00:34:09,250 --> 00:34:10,792
-noticed 'em and I have...
-Oh yeah, I do. What?

800
00:34:10,876 --> 00:34:12,876
You go ahead
and I'll watch the audience.

801
00:34:12,959 --> 00:34:15,626
-(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)
-Well, uh, first of all,

